{#-
  Toast — re-export of the Sonner viewport (Ring 2).

  Toast and Sonner share the same viewport DOM (only the spec entry is
  separate — Toast.md is the consumer-facing API documentation, Sonner.md
  is the engine specification). This two-entry structure keeps discoverability
  for consumers (who search for "toast" by mental model) while letting
  the engine evolve under a stable consumer surface.

  Usage — pick the include path that matches your mental model:

    {% include '@cremona/components/toast/toast.html.twig' %}
    {# or equivalently: #}
    {% include '@cremona/components/sonner/sonner.html.twig' %}

  Both render the same viewport markup. The SonnerController handles
  runtime lifecycle either way.

  When boot() is called from the kit's index.js, the viewport is
  auto-injected by `ensureSonnerViewport()` — most consumers do NOT need
  this include unless they prefer SSR-rendered viewport (e.g. for
  layout stability on long FCP).

  See Sonner (../sonner/sonner.html.twig) for the full markup contract
  (data-controller, data-action, queue indicator child).
-#}
